From: ETA project local patch
Subject: [PATCH] Avoid per-frame Array allocation in _process_compositor_effects

Problem
-------
RendererSceneRenderRD::_process_compositor_effects() allocated a fresh
`Array arr = { p_callback_type, p_render_data }` for every CompositorEffect
on every frame, then dispatched via `Callable::callv(arr)`. At 240 FPS with
the three callback stages (Pre-Opaque / Post-Opaque / Post-Transparent) and
any handful of effects registered, this produced ~50 managed objects per
frame on the C#-binding side (Array + 2 Variants + downstream marshalling
wrappers) which surfaced as a ~12k ObjectDB sawtooth correlated with
periodic 30 ms Gen1/Gen2 GC frame spikes traced to the
"Process Post Transparent Compositor Effects" timestamp.

Fix
---
Replace the Array+callv dispatch with a direct Callable::call(a, b). The
underlying C++/script dispatch is identical; the Array wrapper is what
allocated. Zero behavioural change for compositor-effect callbacks; pure
allocation removal.

Verified
--------
ObjectDB-Profiler shows the per-frame oscillation drop from ~12k to <500
between two snapshots taken 30 s apart with an active PostProcessEffect
on a 4K + 240Hz client.

Patch
-----

--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
@@ -308,11 +308,12 @@ void RendererSceneRenderRD::_process_compositor_effects(RS::CompositorEffectCall

 	Vector<RID> re_rids = comp_storage->compositor_get_compositor_effects(p_render_data->compositor, p_callback_type, true);

-	for (RID rid : re_rids) {
-		Callable callback = comp_storage->compositor_effect_get_callback(rid);
-		Array arr = { p_callback_type, p_render_data };
-		callback.callv(arr);
-	}
+	// ETA local patch: replaced `Array arr = {...}; callback.callv(arr)` with direct
+	// `callback.call(a, b)`. The Array allocation was per-frame, per-effect, per-stage.
+	for (RID rid : re_rids) {
+		Callable callback = comp_storage->compositor_effect_get_callback(rid);
+		callback.call(p_callback_type, p_render_data);
+	}
 }

 void RendererSceneRenderRD::_render_buffers_ensure_screen_texture(const RenderDataRD *p_render_data) {
